import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.hist(data['miles'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Miles Driven')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['miles'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.plot(data['year'], data['miles'], label='Miles')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Gas Mileage')
    plt.title('How has the average gas mileage changed over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='gas', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)

    plt.xlabel('Gas Mileage')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of gas mileage?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    side_counts = data['side'].value_counts()
    side_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'red', 'orange'])
    plt.title('What is the most common side of the road driven on?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Side of the Road')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Left', 'Right', 'Bottom', 'Other'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['miles'], data['gas'], c=data['year'].dt.year, cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Mileage')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between miles driven and gas mileage?', wrap=True)
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Years")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
